name: CGError
desc: A uniform type for result codes returned by functions in Core Graphics.

items.name: case cannotComplete
items.desc: The requested operation is inappropriate for the parameters passed in, or the current system state.

items.name: case illegalArgument
items.desc: One or more of the parameters passed to a function are invalid. Check for NULL pointers.

items.name: case invalidConnection
items.desc: The parameter representing a connection to the window server is invalid.

items.name: case invalidContext
items.desc: The CPSProcessSerNum or context identifier parameter is not valid.

items.name: case invalidOperation
items.desc: The requested operation is not valid for the parameters passed in, or the current system state.

items.name: case noneAvailable
items.desc: The requested operation could not be completed as the indicated resources were not found.

items.name: case notImplemented
items.desc: Return value from obsolete function stubs present for binary compatibility, but not typically called.

items.name: case rangeCheck
items.desc: A parameter passed in has a value that is inappropriate, or which does not map to a useful operation or value.

items.name: case success
items.desc: The requested operation was completed successfully.

items.name: case typeCheck
items.desc: A data type or token was encountered that did not match the expected type or token.
